confirmed most input prices but showed variations in output costs. ### Key Insights - Most platforms offer a mix of per-token and GPU-per-hour pricing models. - License conditions (Apache 2.0) provide significant flexibility for enterprise deployment. - Platforms like Northflank and Fireworks AI emphasize transparent pricing with no rate-limit conditions, appealing to enterprise users. ### Reference Checking - Confirmed from references that Northflank, Fireworks AI, and Hugging Face offer comprehensive deployment solutions with specific pricing models valid as cited. Clarity was also confirmed on Together AI and its feature set even though exact pricing was less explicit. Affordable Platforms for Implementing OpenAI GPT-OSS 120B 1. Fireworks AI Pricing: $0.15 per 1M input tokens, $0.60 per 1M output tokens Key Features: Serverless API with high reliability, no rate limits, designed for single H100 GPU Suitable For: High-throughput deployments with cost-effective scale 2. Together AI Pricing: Competitive API pricing (usually <$1 per 1M tokens) Key Features: Supports a wide range of uses including chat, vision, with flexible API integration Suitable For: Enterprise use and developers requiring broad modality support 3. Northflank Pricing: $5.48 per hour for 2×H100 GPUs; $0.12 for 1M input, $2.42 for 1M output tokens Key Features: One-click deployment, support for Kubernetes, no rate limits Suitable For: Companies needing robust self-hosting solutions 4. Hugging Face Pricing: Pay-as-you-go with managed or self-hosted options Key Features: Flexible deployment, open weights, community GPU for testing Suitable For: Developers needing flexibility between managed and self-hosted solutions 5. Replicate Pricing: $0.18 per 1M input tokens, varied output costs Key Features: Simple REST-based API, suited for medium production use Suitable For: Smaller/medium projects needing straightforward integration Conclusion These platforms cater to varying needs, balancing between cost, enterprise readiness, and infrastructure control. Ensure to cross-verify these prices with current offers online, as they might fluctuate based on available capacity and demand at the time of deployment. Mind Map Expand Pricing Key Features Suitable For Fireworks AI Pricing Key Features Suitable For Together AI Pricing Key Features Suitable For Northflank Pricing Key Features Suitable For Hugging Face Pricing Key Features Suitable For Replicate Platforms cater to varying needs Balance cost and enterprise readiness Cross-verify prices online Conclusion Affordable Platforms for Implementing OpenAI GPT-OSS 120B Best practices for deploying GPT-OSS 120B locally Comparative analysis of open-source AI models Impact of Apache 2.0 licensing on AI implementations Mixture-of-Agents Search Web"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=13b7ba79-bf41-4e04-ab60-5ffac0b4bf41","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=13b7ba79-bf41-4e04-ab60-5ffac0b4bf41"}]}]}]
